com.xuggle.ferry
Class Mutex

java.lang.Object
  com.xuggle.ferry.RefCounted
      com.xuggle.ferry.Mutex

public class Mutex
extends RefCounted

Internal Only.

This object exists so that Native code can get access to thread safe locking objects if they need it.

Implements a blocking Mutually-Exclusive lock by wrapping a Java lock.

If not running inside Java, lock() and unlock() are NO-OPs.

equals

public boolean equals(Object obj)
Compares two values, returning true if the underlying objects in native code are the same object. That means you can have two different Java objects, but when you do a comparison, you'll find out they are the EXACT same object.

Overrides:
